programme.title: Card Sharks
programme.desc: This show from legendary Mark Goodson-Bill Todman Productions features two contestants trying to predict answers to survey questions for the opportunity to play a game with oversized playing cards for a chance to win cash. One contestant guesses how many people (out of 100) gave a certain answer to a question and the other contestant then guesses if the number is higher or lower than the opponent's guess. The winning contestant then faces a row of cards and must determine if each succeeding card is higher or lower than the one that precedes it. The contestant who wins two out of three games wins the match and plays the bonus round, called Money Cards. The Money Cards round is similar to the card game in the main game but with three levels of cards instead of one row. The contestant is given $200 at the beginning of Money Cards and wagers any or all of that money when guessing if the cards will be higher or lower than the previous one. A perfect round could earn the contestant $28,800.

programme.desc: Gene Autry (Gene Autry) is the circuit judge for a small town when recently released convict Ed Wheeler (Kirk Riley) tries to kill a man named Jim Granby (Carleton Young). programme.title: The Last of the Pony Riders
programme.desc: Gene Autry (Gene Autry) works for the Pony Express, which is becoming obsolete due to the rapid onset of modernization, including the telegraph. When Gene brings an innovative idea to his employer, Tom (John Downey), he's fired. Meanwhile, Clyde Vesey (Howard Wright) tries to steal Tom's business by pressuring him to repay a loan and obstructing Pony Express riders. Despite having been fired, Gene follows Clyde's henchmen and tries to stand up for Tom and his family.

programme.title: On Top of Old Smoky
programme.desc: Singing cowboy Gene Autry (Gene Autry) and his sidekick, Smiley (Smiley Burnette), are performing with the Cass County Boys when they're mistaken for Texas Rangers. Despite their protests, they're soon involved in a dispute between tol road owner Jen Larrabee (Gail Davis) and Doc Judson (Grandon Rhodes) over Larrabee's property, which contains mineral deposits. Judson has been trying to coerce Larrabee into selling, but Gene and Smiley are determined to protect her land.

programme.title: Pack Train
programme.desc: Singing cowboy Gene Autry (Gene Autry) and his good pal Dan Coleman (Tom London) agree to help the pioneer residents of Sunshine Valley get much-needed food and medical supplies after the owners of a local store, Ross McLain (Kenne Duncan) and Lola Riker (Sheila Ryan), rip them off. However, getting the goods to the pioneers is a dangerous job. On the way to the valley, Autry -- with his trusty horse, Champion -- and Coleman are attacked by bandits led by the dastardly McLain.

programme.title: Saginaw Trail
programme.desc: Gene Autry (Gene Autry), a mounted ranger, helps protect Michigan settlers from nearby Native American tribes. After learning that a rash of attacks may be connected to a shady fur trapper, Autry sends Smiley (Smiley Burnette) to infiltrate the trapper's gang. Working undercover, Smiley learns that Jules Brissac (Eugene Borden), the area's biggest and most ruthless fur trapper, has been working with the local tribes to scare off the settlers who are ruining his lucrative business.

programme.title: Down Mexico Way
programme.desc: Two alleged movie producers arrive in Sage City and claim that a film will be shot there. Promising to double investments, they collect $35,000 from the townspeople, then flee. Gene Autry (Gene Autry) and his friend Frog (Smiley Burnette) track the crooks to Mexico, where they learn a similar scam is targeting wealthy Don Carlos Alvarado (Julian Rivero) and his daughter, Maria (Fay McKenzie). Rushing to warn the Alvarados, the men meet the producers -- who are not the same men from Sage City.

programme.title: Mule Train
programme.desc: Prospectors have discovered a natural cement mine that yields material of astonishing durability. But greedy contractor Sam Brady (Robert Livingston) enjoys a monopoly on the transportation of crushed rock, which is being used to build a local dam. U.S. Marshal Gene Autry (Gene Autry), however, discovers that Brady has used this method before, and his dams always burst shortly after construction, flooding entire towns. Despite Brady's power, Autry campaigns to have the new dam made of cement.

Gene accepts, despite the corporation's debts, but after a meeting with two corrupt board members, he's told he must raise $50,000 to keep the business alive. Meanwhile, the board members, who want the company for themselves, plot to get Gene in legal trouble.

programme.title: The Librarians
programme.desc: Cued by the popular "The Librarian" trilogy, this series introduces new members of an ancient group protecting mystical artifacts. Hidden below the Metropolitan Public Library, the secret society's longtime leader is Flynn Carsen, whose job has become very complicated. To help, the Library recruits Eve, a counterterrorism agent responsible for organizational security; Jacob, who has encyclopedic knowledge of art, architecture and history; Cassandra, who links auditory/sensory hallucinations to memory; and Ezekiel, a skilled thief and master technician. Overseeing them is Jenkins, the reclusive caretaker of the Library's sleepy little annex in Oregon. Noah Wyle executive produces and recurs as Flynn, the role he played in the movie series.

programme.title: Leverage
programme.desc: Former insurance investigator Nate Ford and his band of cohorts act as modern-day Robin Hoods, pulling elaborate scams targeted against the greedy and the corrupt. programme.title: I'm From Driftwood
programme.desc: Laverne Cox: I'm From Mobile/New Teacher Encounters Homophobia In Second Week/Coming Out Again To Grandma With Alzheimer's/Gender Bending And Runway Walking In A McDonald's Parking Lot/Homeless, Transgender And Finding Her Way/Trans Woman Sacrifices Everything To Finally Be Herself/Transgender High School Student Encounters Cyberbullying/A Broken Down Car, Matching Tattoos, And A Love Story/Agender Person Goes From Being Bullied In The Newark Projects To Gracing The Cover of French Vogue/ Alan Cumming: True Bisexual Stories S1 E1-10 | Laverne Cox remembers the bullying she experienced as a child, and how it's similar to the transphobia she experiences as an adult. Alexa moved from New York City to small-town Jackson, Mississippi, to teach at an under-priveleged school. After only two weeks in, Alexa had to challenge homophobia in the hallway, and had some surprising success. Megan's grandma was supportive and excited when she found out Megan was a lesbian. But after showing signs of Alzheimer's, Megan's grandma forgot and kept asking her if she was seeing any special boy. Megan received a special phone call from her grandma, though, that she'll remember forever. Jacob Tobia, activist for genderqueer, gender non-conforming, and transgender issues, bought a single pair of black pumps while organizing a Gender Nonconforming Day for their high school, a small act that would change the course of their life. After being kicked out of her home at 17, Angela Louis struggled with homelessness, abusive relationships, sex work, and depression, all while transitioning, but nothing could stop her from finding her own path and earning her diploma. Mila Jam had it all, or so she thought. Her drag persona, Britney Houston, had a massive YouTube following and she performed on a hit TV show in London. But she gave it all up so that she could finally live her truth as a woman and as herself. Olivia Page was brave enough to transition in high school. Unfortunately, a classmate decided to cyberbully her on Facebook. Olivia also had the support and kindness of a teacher who helped her through high school. A wild series of events led Sam to meeting the love of her life. Andre J. wants to tell you one thing: Love Yourself. That's how Andre went from being bullied in the projects to appearing on the cover of French Vogue. Alan Cumming remembers when he first felt an attraction to guys and how he came out to American media in a big way. Externals

programme.title: Engaged

programme.title: Drag Kids
programme.desc: Drag has always been about breaking down barriers and daring to do the unexpected. Now, a new type of queen is on the scene: shes fierce, shes living in a time of unprecedented access to queer culture, and shes younger than ever before. Shes a drag kid and shes a long way from the era of the queens who led the Stonewall Riots nearly 50 years ago. Stephan, Jason, Bracken and Nemis have never met, but theyre united by a shared passion for drag. They are about to come together for the first time to perform Lady Gagas Born This Way at the world-famous Montreal Pride Festival. As they prepare for the big show, each faces their own unique challenges, as well as challenges they have in common - deep feelings of isolation and the struggle of trying to claim a place of your own on the fringes of a fringe culture. Drag Kids is a beautiful, daring, and touching portrait of four kids chasing freedom and friendship through the art of drag.

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of dialogues featuring Rosie ODonnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately ones past can dictate their future.
